# Azure Deployment Plan for ZavaStorefront Project

## **Goal**
Provision Azure infrastructure for the ZavaStorefront web application (dev environment) into a single resource group in westus3. Use Bicep files and AZD to define and deploy all resources together. Application to be deployed as a Docker container to Linux App Service (Web App for Containers), without requiring local Docker. App Service will pull images from Azure Container Registry (ACR) using Azure RBAC and managed identity (no password secrets).

## **Project Information**

**ZavaStorefront**  
- **Stack**: ASP.NET Core 6.0 MVC  
- **Type**: E-commerce storefront web application with shopping cart functionality  
- **Containerization**: Docker container-based deployment  
- **Dependencies**: Session-based storage (no external database), Application Insights for monitoring  
- **Hosting**: Azure App Service (Linux/Container)  
- **AI Services**: Microsoft Foundry for GPT-4 and Phi models

## **Azure Resources Architecture**

> **Install the mermaid extension in IDE to view the architecture.**

```mermaid
graph TD
%% Services
svcazureappservice_webapp["`Name: webapp
Path: src
Language: dotnet
Port: 80`"]

subgraph "Compute Resources"
%% Resources
azureappservice_webapp("`webapp (Azure App Service - Linux Container)`")
end

subgraph "Dependency Resources"
%% Dependency Resources
azurecontainerregistry_acr["`acr (Azure Container Registry)`"]
azureapplicationinsights_appinsights["`appinsights (Azure Application Insights)`"]
foundry_ai["`Microsoft Foundry (AI Services)`"]
end

subgraph "Supporting Services"
loganalytics["`Log Analytics Workspace`"]
managed_identity["`User-Assigned Managed Identity`"]
end

%% Relationships
svcazureappservice_webapp --> |"hosted on"| azureappservice_webapp
azureappservice_webapp -.-> |"system-identity (AcrPull)"| azurecontainerregistry_acr
azureappservice_webapp -.-> |"connection string"| azureapplicationinsights_appinsights
azureappservice_webapp -.-> |"API key"| foundry_ai
azureapplicationinsights_appinsights -.-> |"logs to"| loganalytics
azureappservice_webapp -.-> |"uses"| managed_identity
managed_identity -.-> |"AcrPull role"| azurecontainerregistry_acr
```

**Architecture Summary:**
- The Azure App Service (Linux Container) hosts the ZavaStorefront .NET web application
- The App Service uses a system-assigned managed identity with AcrPull role to pull Docker images from Azure Container Registry (no passwords)
- Application Insights monitors the web application performance and logs
- Log Analytics Workspace stores all diagnostic and monitoring data
- Microsoft Foundry provides access to GPT-4 and Phi AI models in westus3 region

## **Expected Azure Resources**

### Application: ZavaStorefront Web App
- **Hosting Service Type**: Azure App Service (Linux - Web App for Containers)
- **SKU**: B1 (Basic) or higher
  - Performance: 1.75 GB RAM, 1 vCPU
  - Suitable for dev/test workloads
  - Can scale up to higher tiers (S1/P1V2) for production
- **Configuration**:
  - Language: .NET 6.0
  - OS: Linux
  - Container: Enabled (pulls from ACR)
  - Port: 80
  - Environment Variables:
    - `APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING`: Application Insights connection string
    - `AZURE_FOUNDRY_ENDPOINT`: Microsoft Foundry endpoint URL
    - `AZURE_FOUNDRY_API_KEY`: Microsoft Foundry API key (stored in Key Vault)
    - `WEBSITES_PORT`: "80"
  
- **Dependencies Resources**:

  **1. Azure Container Registry**
  - **SKU**: Basic
    - Performance: 10 GB storage, suitable for dev/test scenarios
  - **Service Type**: Azure Container Registry (ACR)
  - **Connection Type**: System-assigned managed identity with AcrPull role
  - **Environment Variables**: 
    - `DOCKER_REGISTRY_SERVER_URL`: ACR login server URL
    - Authentication: Managed Identity (no username/password)

  **2. Application Insights**
  - **SKU**: Standard (pay-as-you-go)
    - Performance: Unlimited ingestion, 90-day retention by default
  - **Service Type**: Azure Application Insights
  - **Connection Type**: Connection string
  - **Environment Variables**:
    - `APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING`: Connection string for telemetry

  **3. Microsoft Foundry**
  - **SKU**: Standard (deployment-based pricing)
  - **Service Type**: Microsoft Foundry (Cognitive Services)
  - **Region**: westus3 (required for GPT-4 and Phi availability)
  - **Models**: GPT-4, Phi
  - **Connection Type**: API Key
  - **Environment Variables**:
    - `AZURE_FOUNDRY_ENDPOINT`: Foundry endpoint
    - `AZURE_FOUNDRY_API_KEY`: API key (reference from Key Vault)

## **Expected Supporting Services**

- **Application Insights**: 
  - Monitors web app performance, exceptions, and user behavior
  - Connected to Log Analytics Workspace

- **User-Assigned Managed Identity**: 
  - Assigned to App Service for secure authentication
  - Has AcrPull role on Container Registry
  - Has Key Vault Secrets User role on Key Vault

- **Log Analytics Workspace**: 
  - Centralized logging for all resources
  - Connected to Application Insights
  - Retention: 30 days (configurable)

- **Key Vault**: 
  - Stores sensitive configuration values
  - Stores Microsoft Foundry API key
  - Access controlled via managed identity

## **Expected Security Configurations**

- **Managed Identity Permissions**:
  - System-assigned managed identity on App Service has AcrPull role on ACR
  - User-assigned managed identity has Key Vault Secrets User role on Key Vault
  - No password-based authentication for ACR access

- **Key Vault Access**:
  - User-Assigned Managed Identity must have "Key Vault Secrets User" role
  - App Service references secrets via @Microsoft.KeyVault() syntax

- **Network Security**:
  - ACR: Private endpoint optional (can be enabled for production)
  - App Service: HTTPS only enforced
  - Foundry: API key authentication

- **RBAC Assignments**:
  - App Service managed identity → AcrPull role → Container Registry
  - App Service managed identity → Key Vault Secrets User → Key Vault

## **Execution Steps**

> **Below are the steps for Copilot to follow; ask Copilot to update or execute this plan.**

### 1. Create Azure Infrastructure Files for AZD

1. **Provisioning tool**: AZD
   - Expected files: `azure.yaml`, `infra/main.bicep`, `infra/main.parameters.json`
   
2. **Get Available Regions and SKUs**:
   - [ ] Call tool `appmod-get-available-region-sku` to get available regions and SKUs for:
     - Microsoft.Web/sites (App Service)
     - Microsoft.ContainerRegistry/registries (ACR)
     - Microsoft.Insights/components (Application Insights)
     - Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts (Microsoft Foundry)
   - Verify westus3 availability for all resources

3. **Check Existing Files**:
   - [ ] Check if azure.yaml, infra/main.bicep, infra/main.parameters.json exist
   - **If files exist**:
     - Existing file paths: (to be determined)
     - Validate that resources match requirements
     - Add/update resources as needed
     - Generating Files: No (updating only)
   - **If files do not exist**:
     - [ ] Call tool `appmod-get-iac-rules` to get rules for Bicep generation
     - [ ] Generate azure.yaml with service configuration
     - [ ] Generate infra/main.bicep with all required resources
     - [ ] Generate infra/main.parameters.json with parameters
     - [ ] Call `get_errors` on generated files and fix any issues
     - Generating Files: azure.yaml, infra/main.bicep, infra/main.parameters.json

4. **Validate Bicep Files**:
   - [ ] Use `get_errors` tool to check for Bicep syntax errors
   - [ ] Fix any errors and retry validation
   - [ ] Ensure RBAC role assignments are correctly defined

### 2. Environment Setup for AZD

1. **Install Tools**:
   - [ ] Check if Azure CLI (az) is installed; install if needed
   - [ ] Check if AZD CLI is installed; install if needed
   - [ ] Verify both tools are in PATH and functional

2. **Create AZD Environment**:
   - [ ] Run `azd env new zavastore-dev --no-prompt` to create environment
   - [ ] If environment exists, verify it matches requirements

3. **Set Environment Variables**:
   - [ ] Review infra/main.bicep and infra/main.parameters.json for required variables
   - [ ] Set using `azd env set <key> <value>`:
     - `AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID`: (from az account show)
     - `AZURE_LOCATION`: westus3
     - `AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP`: rg-zavastore-dev-westus3
     - `AZURE_ENV_NAME`: zavastore-dev
   
4. **Set Subscription**:
   - [ ] Use default subscription from `az account show`
   - [ ] Or set specific subscription: `az account set --subscription <id>`

5. **Create Resource Group**:
   - [ ] Verify Bicep deployment scope (resource group level)
   - [ ] Create resource group: `az group create --name rg-zavastore-dev-westus3 --location westus3`

### 3. Deployment

1. **Dry Run (Preview)**:
   - [ ] Run `azd provision --preview --no-prompt` to validate infrastructure
   - [ ] Review the preview output for any warnings or errors
   - [ ] Fix any issues and re-run preview

2. **Provision and Deploy**:
   - [ ] Run `azd up --no-prompt` to provision infrastructure and deploy app
   - [ ] Monitor deployment progress
   - [ ] If errors occur:
     - Review error messages
     - Fix Bicep/configuration issues
     - Retry deployment

3. **Deployment Validation**:
   - [ ] Call tool `appmod-get-azd-app-logs` to check application logs
   - [ ] Verify App Service is running and healthy
   - [ ] Test the application URL
   - [ ] Verify Application Insights is receiving telemetry
   - [ ] Confirm managed identity has ACR pull permissions

### 4. Summarize Result

1. **Generate Summary**:
   - [ ] Use `appmod-summarize-result` tool to create deployment summary
   - [ ] Include:
     - All provisioned resource names and URLs
     - App Service URL
     - ACR name
     - Application Insights instrumentation key
     - Microsoft Foundry endpoint
   - Generating files: `.azure/summary.copilotmd`

## **Progress Tracking**

Progress will be tracked in `.azure/progress.copilotmd` with the following format:

- [ ] Create Azure Infrastructure Files for AZD
  - [ ] Get available regions and SKUs
  - [ ] Generate or validate azure.yaml
  - [ ] Generate or validate infra/main.bicep
  - [ ] Generate or validate infra/main.parameters.json
  - [ ] Fix any errors

- [ ] Environment Setup for AZD
  - [ ] Install Azure CLI
  - [ ] Install AZD CLI
  - [ ] Create AZD environment
  - [ ] Set environment variables
  - [ ] Create resource group

- [ ] Deployment
  - [ ] Run provision preview
  - [ ] Run azd up
  - [ ] Validate deployment
  - [ ] Test application

- [ ] Summarize Result
  - [ ] Generate deployment summary
  - [ ] Document resource URLs

## **Tools Checklist**

Copilot MUST call the following tools as specified in the Execution Steps:

- [ ] `appmod-get-available-region-sku` - Get available regions and SKUs for Azure resources
- [ ] `appmod-get-iac-rules` - Get IaC generation rules for Bicep
- [ ] `get_errors` - Validate generated Bicep files for errors
- [ ] `appmod-get-azd-app-logs` - Retrieve application logs after deployment
- [ ] `appmod-summarize-result` - Generate deployment summary report

## **Success Criteria**

✅ All Azure resources provisioned successfully in westus3 region  
✅ App Service running with Docker container from ACR  
✅ Managed identity authentication working (no password secrets)  
✅ Application Insights collecting telemetry  
✅ Microsoft Foundry accessible for GPT-4 and Phi  
✅ Application accessible via HTTPS  
✅ All security configurations in place
